MEDICATION FOLLOW-UP
CHIEF COMPLAINT:
Manav Agarwal is a 34 Y male, returns for medication management.
UPDATED CLINICAL STATUS/MED RESPONSE:
Reports did contact Alameda Alliance re CD treatment. Had couple of appts with them. Pt reports that he was told that in order for them to treat him and consider medications, he'd need to change over from Kaiser to them altogether, not just CD services. Reports was told that pt did not meet criteria for inpt rehab.
Has been med compliant. Reports only been taking the gabapentin at night prn sleep as it's too sedating to take during day for anxiety. Interested in trying the buspirone for anxiety at this point.
Reports it has been stressful as is taking summer classes and the pace is faster in the summer. Some trouble with conc/focus.
Denies d&a use since l/v. Denies suicidal ideation.
OBJECTIVE:
Psychiatric Medications As of Last Contact:
cymbalta 30mg 3 daily
Naltrexone 50mg daily
Gabapentin - try dec to 200mg tid prn anxiety - pt reports has tablets that he can try cutting.
Side Effects: see above
cymbalta 2019 - self d/c due to inc in trouble with conc, then restarted per pt request.
Mirtazapine briefly '19 - tired, sleepy.
effexor xr briefly '18 - did help but bothered by tiredness and restless leg
Gabapentin 100mg briefly '18 - ha's and didn't find helpful.
prozac 10-20mg/day - relatively stable, wanted to try off med.
Lorazepam 1mg - for sleep - lasted too long, not as alert next day, prefers temazepam.
prozac 30mg/day - inc anxiety, insomnia, gi. zoloft 50mg - more tired, gi.
(trazodone - not helped. ritalin - tried/crash in bet dose/inc in anxiety. ambien - did not like)
(celexa - blurred vision, constipation. Tried Strattera in college briefly - didn't help.
lexapro - '12-'13)
